                <h2>PRP Injection Results Timeline</h2>
                <p>PRP is not an overnight solution. It works by triggering your body's natural regenerative processes, which take time. Here is a realistic timeline of what to expect:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Initial inflammatory response at the injection site (this is normal and desired). You may notice mild redness or swelling that subsides quickly.</li>
                    <li><strong>Week 3-4:</strong> Growth factors begin stimulating cell proliferation. For hair treatments, shedding may temporarily reduce. Skin may start to feel smoother.</li>
                    <li><strong>Month 2-3:</strong> Collagen production ramps up. Hair follicles enter the active growth phase. Skin texture and tone begin to visibly improve. Joint pain patients may notice reduced stiffness.</li>
                    <li><strong>Month 3-6:</strong> Peak results become visible. New hair growth is noticeable. Facial skin appears firmer and more radiant. Joint mobility continues to improve.</li>
                    <li><strong>Month 6-12:</strong> Full results are established. With maintenance sessions, improvements continue to build over time.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>It is important to understand that individual results vary. Factors like age, overall health, severity of the condition, and adherence to aftercare instructions all influence the outcome. Patients who complete the full recommended course of sessions consistently see the best results.</p>

